\begin_layout Section
Revamped website
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Summary
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Presently, the DEN website is not current in content nor style.
 A saying among programmers is that an obsolete comment is worse than no
 comment at all, and the same applies to our website.
 With Dr.
 Wolffe's help, I will provide current content for the site.
 In addition, the styling for the DEN website is quite archaic.
 As a function of the computer science department, the DEN should have a
 website that is atractive and usable, and a shining example of a well-designed
 site.
 As part of the website update, the style of the site will be upgraded to
 reflect current practices.
 Possibly the most important reason to update the site is that former DEN
 students have referenced the DEN on their resume and supplied the URL to
 the DEN website.
 Potential employers who have checked the website for mentioned projects
 or papers have been surprised to find them missing.
\end_layout

