\begin_layout Section
Showcase project
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Summary
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
An important part of this graduate assistantship for me is increasing the
 visibility of the DEN, both at Grand Valley and publicly.
 One way of accomplishing this is by creating a piece of software that would
 be useful to many people, especially those in academia.
 In our CIS 678 Machine Learning course, I recently undertook a project
 in which I implemented a CpG island finder using Hidden Markov Models.
 Although there is an abundance of documentation explaining the CpG islands
 problem, I was surprised by the lack of current software implementing the
 solution, especially using the Hidden Markov Model approach.
 For this project, I would like to develop a web-accessible CpG island finder
 program.
 Furthermore, the execution of Hidden Markov Models can be accelerated through
 parallel processing.
 I would like to implement my program such that it can take advantage of
 the advanced graphics cards and multi-processor architectures present in
 the DEN.
 The program could be made available for running in-browser on the DEN website,
 and the code could be hosted inside our DEN code repository.
 The program and source code would serve as an example of the types of projects
 that are undertaken in the DEN.
\end_layout

